## Domain: vanilla-derivation

### Requirement: Vanilla Asset Copy

The system MUST provide a `vanilla.nix` derivation that copies all upstream gentle-ai assets without any local modifications. This includes: AGENTS.md, opencode assets (skills, commands, plugins, persona, opencode.json template), root-level skills, and agent-specific configurations (claude, cursor, etc.).

#### Scenario: Vanilla build contains only upstream files

- GIVEN `vanilla.nix` is built with `nix build .#gentle-ai-assets-vanilla`
- WHEN the output directory is inspected
- THEN no `localPersonaRules` content is present in any file
- AND no `extraSkills` from `modules/home/opencode/skills` are present
- AND all files match upstream source exactly

#### Scenario: All upstream skills present

- GIVEN upstream repo contains 16 skills in `internal/assets/skills/`
- WHEN vanilla derivation is built
- THEN all 16 skills are copied to `$out/share/gentle-ai/skills/`
- AND skill directory structure is preserved

#### Scenario: All upstream commands present

- GIVEN upstream repo contains 10 commands
- WHEN vanilla derivation is built
- THEN all 10 commands are present in the output
- AND command files are unmodified from upstream

#### Scenario: TDD strict files included

- GIVEN upstream repo contains `strict-tdd.md` and `strict-tdd-verify.md`
- WHEN vanilla derivation is built
- THEN both files are present in the output
- AND file contents match upstream exactly

#### Scenario: No local modifications applied

- GIVEN vanilla.nix is evaluated
- WHEN the derivation is inspected
- THEN `localPersonaRules` parameter does not exist
- AND `extraSkills` parameter does not exist
- AND `installPhase` contains only `cp` operations, no `cat` concatenation or `substituteInPlace`

